  "text": "The CSS style change propagation through Chromium's Blink rendering pipeline follows these key stages:\n\n1. **Style Resolution Stage**: The `StyleResolver` class (located in `third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h`) is the entry point for resolving computed styles for DOM elements. The `ResolveStyle()` method (line 71) processes CSS cascade rules and computes the final ComputedStyle for elements based on the document's stylesheets (user styles, author styles, and UA styles). This class maintains a 1-1 relationship with the Document.\n\n2. **Layout Tree Stage**: The `LayoutObject` class (located in `third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h`) is the base class for the layout tree. As described in the header (line 177), LayoutObjects form a tree structure closely mapping the DOM tree, with LayoutView as the root. The layout tree is built from the computed styles and performs layout (sizing and positioning) of elements. The layout results are stored for painting and hit-testing.\n\n3. **Painting Layer Stage**: The `PaintLayer` class (located in `third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h`) provides a painting layer abstraction for complex rendering operations (opacity, clipping, filters, reflections, etc.). As described (line 107), PaintLayer handles hardware acceleration through compositing, scrolling, and various performance optimizations. It manages the painting order and applies complex paint operations that cannot be handled by the base LayoutObject.\n\n4. **Paint Command Recording Stage**: The `PaintController` class (located in `third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h`) is responsible for processing display items as they are produced and generating the final paint artifact. It includes logic for caching, cache invalidation, and merging paint operations (line 131).\n\n5. **Display List Stage**: The `DisplayItemList` class (located in `third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.h`) serves as a container for a list of display items of various types (line 28). The PaintController uses DisplayItemList to record and manage the sequence of paint operations that will ultimately be rasterized.\n\nThe full rendering pipeline flow is: CSS Style → StyleResolver → ComputedStyle → LayoutObject (layout tree) → PaintLayer (painting abstraction) → PaintController (paint command recording) → DisplayItemList (display item container) → Rasterization."
}

